main event: Two oval, shiny objects were observed descending at a steep angle over Moses Lake, Washington, on 5 October 1962.
interesting points: The objects were seen descending at a steep angle before stopping and moving laterally at a rapid pace., Local investigators initially considered reflections as the cause of the sighting., Witnesses evaluated the sightings in terms of altitude and azimuth., The objects were thought to be traveling at speeds exceeding Mach 5., The sighting lasted between 2 to 30 seconds and involved two confirmed observations.
witness description: Local investigators and observers near Moses Lake
